Ethan Bates, for example, another senior in the solar energy training class, is the son of a mine foreman who lost his job when the Bowie Mine outside Paonia closed in 2016.
In the past four years, the class has helped install two solar arrays behind Delta High School.
Solar Energy International, a local nonprofit and a major catalyst behind the Delta class, is working to integrate solar training into science curriculum across the region.
Through SEI, the co-op has administered grants for Gravesâ€™ class, and it funds solar trainings for teachers across the area.
In the hallways, every other light fixture is dark, the bulbs removed by solar students.